      "type": "verse",
      "number": "1"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I ask Thee for a thoughtful love, through constant watching wise,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "To meet the glad with joyful smiles, and to wipe the weeping eyes;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And a heart at leisure from itself, to soothe and sympathize."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "2"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I would not have the restless will that hurries to and fro,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Seeking for some great thing to do or secret thing to know;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I would be treated as a child, and guided where I go."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "3"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Wherever in the world I am, in whatso’er estate,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I have a fellowship with hearts to keep and cultivate;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And a work of lowly love to do for the Lord on whom I wait."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "4"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "So I ask Thee for the daily strength, to none that ask denied,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And a mind to blend with outward life while keeping at Thy side;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "Content to fill a little space, if Thou be glorified."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "5"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And if some things I do not ask in my cup of blessing be,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "I would have my spirit filled the more with grateful love to Thee,"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "More careful, not to serve Thee much, but to please Thee perfectly."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "6"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "There are briers besetting every path that call for patient care;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "There is a cross in every lot, and an earnest need for prayer;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "But a lowly heart that leans on Thee is happy anywhere."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "7"
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "In a service which Thy will appoints there are no bonds for me;"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "For my inmost heart is taught “the truth” that makes Thy children “free”"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "segments": [
            {
              "chord": "",
              "text": "And a life of self-renouncing love is a life of liberty."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "verse",
      "number": "8"
    }
  ],
